Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%grams} on a #baking tray{} in a single
layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet},
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Bake on the top shelf, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

In a #large bowl{}, combine the garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for both amounts), then
add the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized
balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray.

When the chips are about halfway through cooking, bake on the middle shelf
until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the burgers bake, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the
@Cider Vinegar{15%milliliters}, a pinch of @?sugar{} and a drizzle of @oil{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside for now.

Meanwhile, when the burgers have ~{5%minutes} left, pop a #small saucepan{}
on medium-high heat with the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Honey{15%grams} and
@Water{100%milliliters} for the sauce (see pantry for amount).

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water
> for 1 min to loosen.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat to medium and simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{30%grams} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Just before everything's ready, toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} through the
dressing.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Transfer the naked burgers to your plates. Spoon over the gochujang sauce
(reheat if needed) and sprinkle on the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

Serve the spiced chips and salad alongside.

Enjoy!